# Model Evaluation Fundamentals

**How do we know if our model is actually good?**

| Metric | Purpose | Best For |
|--------|---------|----------|
| **Accuracy** | Overall correctness | Balanced datasets |
| **Precision** | Avoiding false positives | Spam detection |
| **Recall** | Catching all positives | Medical diagnosis |
| **F1-Score** | Balance precision/recall | General use |

**Key Insight:** Never trust a model you haven't tested properly

@notes:
- Evaluation prevents overconfidence
- Different metrics for different priorities
- Medical diagnosis example - can't miss diseases
- Spam detection - don't block important emails

